Ada’s hands stopped the water. Luggage was being bumped down all over the flat.

“I’m not looking,” said Lucette idiotically, “I only dropped in for my box.”

“Please, tip them, pet,” said Van, a compulsive tipper—“And pass me that towel,” added Ada, but the ancilla was picking up coins she had spilled in her haste, and Ada now saw in her turn Van’s scarlet ladder of sutures—“Oh my poor darling,” she cried, and out of sheer compassion allowed him the repeat